<b>Laxoox</b> (pronounced 'laa-h≈çh' in <language wordnetid="106282651" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../357/441357.xml">
Somali</link></language>
) or <b>Canjeero</b> IPA:&nbsp; is a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../472/210472.xml">
pancake</link>-like bread eaten in <country wordnetid="108544813" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../358/27358.xml">
Somalia</link></country>
, <country wordnetid="108544813" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../794/17207794.xml">
Djibouti</link></country>
, and <country wordnetid="108544813" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../939/350939.xml">
Yemen</link></country>
. It was also brought to the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../140/11447140.xml">
Israeli cuisine</link> by <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../787/348787.xml">
Yemenite Jews</link>.
